---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About | Lost Unfound Records">
  <div class="page-section">
    <p class="text-label">Who we are</p>
    <h1 class="text-display">Two people.<br />One room.</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      Lost Unfound is a recording and production studio built around a simple idea: the best records come from
      genuine collaboration between people who trust each other. We're based in the Forlì / Bologna area of Italy,
      and we work with artists who take their music seriously.
    </p>

    <div class="profiles">
      <article class="profile">
        <div class="profile-img-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519681393784-d120267933ba?w=600&q=80"
            alt="Alessandro Pelosio"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="profile-text">
          <h2 class="text-heading">Alessandro Pelosio</h2>
          <p class="text-label role">Producer · Sound Engineer · Mixer</p>
          <p>
            Alessandro has been recording and producing music for over a decade. His background spans studio
            engineering, live sound, and electronic music production — which means he thinks about a record both
            as a sound object and as a live experience. He has a particular interest in the relationship between
            room acoustics and recorded tone, and a near-obsessive approach to low-frequency balance.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside the studio he plays guitar badly and reads about analogue signal processing. He is the reason
            the studio has too many microphones.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="profile reverse">
        <div class="profile-img-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1470225620780-dba8ba36b745?w=600&q=80"
            alt="Davide Bacchi"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="profile-text">
          <h2 class="text-heading">Davide Bacchi</h2>
          <p class="text-label role">Songwriter · Producer · Assistant Engineer</p>
          <p>
            Davide approaches production from the songwriter's perspective first. Before any technical decisions
            are made, he asks whether the arrangement is serving the song. His strength is in finding what a track
            needs and removing what it doesn't — a discipline that often produces more impactful results than adding.
          </p>
          <p>
            He has written and produced for artists across indie pop, folk, and experimental genres. He is the
            reason the studio occasionally smells of very good coffee.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro {
    max-width: 70ch;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-block: 2rem 4rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-block: 1rem 0;
  }

  .profiles {
    display: grid;
    gap: 6rem;
  }

  .profile {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .profile.reverse {
    grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr;
  }

  .profile.reverse .profile-img-wrap {
    order: 2;
  }

  .profile.reverse .profile-text {
    order: 1;
  }

  .profile-img-wrap {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .profile-img-wrap img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    filter: grayscale(30%);
  }

  .role {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-block: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
</style>
